search:Testing Spring Boot + Kafka-Sprin.content:
- Use `mvn clean install` to build your project.
- Ensure Kafka is running locally or use Docker with `docker run -d --name kafka -p 9092:9092 wurstmeister/kafka`.
- For testing, include dependencies like `spring-kafka-test`, `testcontainers-kafka`.
- Use `@EmbeddedKafka` for in-memory Kafka server.
- Configure Kafka properties in `application.properties` or `application.yml`.
- Example of a test case:
  ```java
  @SpringBootTest
  public class KafkaListenerTest {
      @Autowired
      private KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate;

      @Test
      public void testKafkaListener() throws Exception {
          // Send message to topic
          kafkaTemplate.send("test-topic", "Hello, Kafka!");

          // Add assertions to verify listener received the message
      }
  }
  ```
- Use `@Container` from Testcontainers for more complex setups.
- Ensure your Kafka topics are created before tests run.
